            "Calendar management for daily activities",
            "Character-driven narrative with multiple endings"
        ],
        "long_description": "Persona 4 is a Japanese role-playing game developed by Atlus. The story follows a group of students at Yasogami High School who uncover a mystery surrounding missing persons linked to the Midnight Channel\u2014a mysterious TV phenomenon. They are transported to the TV World, where they battle Shadows using Personas\u2014manifestations of their psyche. The game features a calendar-based system that allows players to manage school days and social relationships (Social Links), which enhance combat abilities and story progression. Released for PlayStation 2 in 2008, it has since been re-released as Persona 4 Golden on multiple platforms including Nintendo Switch, PlayStation 4, Xbox One, and PC via Steam.",
        "legacy_and_impact": [
            "Pioneered the integration of social simulation elements into JRPGs",
            "Influenced numerous subsequent games in the genre with its narrative depth",
            "Widely regarded as one of the greatest RPGs of all time"
        ]
